# GitHub Packages scope→registry mappings (ADR-004). Both orgs' scoped packages
# resolve from npm.pkg.github.com. These lines ARE honored by pnpm.
@theamazingwolf:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
@stormforgeventures:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com

# NOTE: pnpm deliberately IGNORES an `_authToken` line in a committed project .npmrc
# (it won't expand ${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN} from a checked-in file — anti-leak). So auth is
# NOT configured here. Supply it out-of-band:
#   • locally  — put `//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=<PAT>` in your user ~/.npmrc
#                (or run: pnpm config set "//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken" <PAT>)
#   • CI       — a step writes ~/.npmrc from a secret before install (needed once
#                @theamazingwolf/sport-* deps land — PRD-002 §2.0; GITHUB_TOKEN can't
#                read that org, so use a cross-org read:packages PAT, e.g. SPORT_PACKAGES_TOKEN).
# Today nothing here fetches from the registry (both @stormforgeventures packages are
# workspace-local), so no token is required yet.
